WEBVTT

00:19.978 --> 00:21.938
Geon-woo, slow down.

00:29.529 --> 00:32.073
NOVEMBER 4, 2008
LIM NA-RI

00:37.078 --> 00:38.329
Cheers!

00:41.624 --> 00:42.542
Cheers!

00:48.798 --> 00:50.133
Ugh!

00:50.216 --> 00:53.595
Tell me about this boy of yours.
What's his name? What's his deal?

00:53.678 --> 00:55.597
Geon-woo. He's beyond!

00:55.680 --> 00:57.307
Show me a picture then.

00:57.807 --> 01:00.852
Let me see if he looks good enough
and worth this heartbreak.

01:00.935 --> 01:02.479
Otherwise, dump him.

01:02.562 --> 01:04.481
That's horseshit.

01:05.065 --> 01:06.941
I'm sure you won't be disappointed.

01:09.986 --> 01:13.740
-Hey, he's really handsome.
-Right?

01:15.241 --> 01:17.619
Come on, he's just okay.
He's nothing special.

01:17.702 --> 01:19.079
What are you talking about?

01:19.162 --> 01:22.290
If we put the two of you side by side,
you'd look like a troll.

01:25.668 --> 01:29.964
-And this guy? That's the otaku loser?
-You can tell that from one photo?

01:30.590 --> 01:33.551
Oh shit. That just confirms
he's a pathetic loser.

01:33.635 --> 01:36.221
You should see
how he lives up to his looks.

01:36.304 --> 01:37.764
Here, give it to me.

01:38.515 --> 01:40.266
Look at this.

01:44.187 --> 01:48.441
He thinks
that this little wish app is real!

01:49.484 --> 01:53.446
Holy shit! Okay, this thing
isn't the magic lamp from Aladdin.

01:53.530 --> 01:56.908
He's a high-schooler who believes
this shit. Grants wishes, my ass.

01:56.991 --> 01:59.119
He also gossips about Geon-woo and Se-ah.

01:59.202 --> 02:01.996
This app you're talking about
that grants you wishes,

02:02.705 --> 02:04.082
is it called Girigo?

02:04.165 --> 02:06.626
What the hell? You heard of it too?

02:10.296 --> 02:11.214
Hey.

02:15.760 --> 02:17.637
Yeah, I know about Girigo.

02:18.179 --> 02:19.180
It's no joke.

02:19.264 --> 02:21.599
Oh, for fuck's sake.

02:21.683 --> 02:24.310
-Are you drunk?
-We're just having a conversation.

02:25.436 --> 02:27.063
Once you make your wish,

02:27.564 --> 02:29.440
you have to die for it to come true.

02:29.524 --> 02:30.984
You're so full of shit.

02:31.067 --> 02:32.318
Just remember that.

02:39.284 --> 02:41.578
Admit it, I got you! Your face!

02:41.661 --> 02:43.413
Oh, man, she's still a kid.

02:43.913 --> 02:46.916
Why the hell are we hanging out
with this baby?

02:47.000 --> 02:49.544
Hey, don't be scared.
It's all right. Here.

02:50.170 --> 02:54.257
Anyway, that app was made by these guys
so they could mess with someone.

02:54.340 --> 02:55.592
You're talking nonsense.

02:55.675 --> 02:58.678
What do you mean, "nonsense"?
It was created to totally fuck up a loser.

02:58.761 --> 03:00.847
Stop!

03:04.392 --> 03:08.438
You know, you normally
give off Kwon Si-won vibes,

03:08.521 --> 03:10.481
but now I see more Do Hye-ryung in you.

03:10.565 --> 03:12.025
Yes, or no?

03:12.108 --> 03:13.651
You're so boring!

03:13.735 --> 03:15.111
Whoa!

03:15.612 --> 03:19.616
-You know it's true they died back then.
-Does anyone care? No.

03:22.285 --> 03:23.453
Na-ri…

03:24.579 --> 03:27.373
-You totally killed the vibe, asshole!
-What did I do?

03:27.457 --> 03:29.542
He didn't! Hey, you wanna play?

03:38.426 --> 03:39.385
What's that?

03:44.891 --> 03:46.309
I think it's my turn.

03:46.392 --> 03:49.771
Since you said
I remind you of a loser, huh?

03:51.564 --> 03:53.524
I think I'm gonna have a go,

03:53.608 --> 03:55.735
and make a wish for me.

03:57.737 --> 04:01.199
GIRIGO
THE APP THAT GRANTS WISHES!

04:01.282 --> 04:04.494
By the way,
does this thing kill people for you?

04:06.788 --> 04:10.583
If I'm offering my life, then it should
be able to do that at least.

04:10.667 --> 04:12.168
Stop it.

04:13.253 --> 04:14.170
GIRIGO
MAKE A WISH

04:21.302 --> 04:26.099
There are two people I want dead. Okay?

04:26.182 --> 04:27.517
Are you fucking crazy?

04:27.600 --> 04:29.435
First is Choi Hyeong-wook.

04:29.519 --> 04:31.521
You're a given.

04:32.772 --> 04:34.816
And the next is Dong-jae,

04:34.899 --> 04:38.486
pissing me off, and been a jerk all night,
and won't shut up!

05:03.094 --> 05:05.013
Oh, I feel like shit.

05:06.848 --> 05:08.308
God, my head is killing me.

05:08.391 --> 05:09.600
Ow!

05:09.684 --> 05:10.935
Hey!

05:15.565 --> 05:18.234
Seriously, what an annoying
start to the day.

05:19.110 --> 05:20.528
Listen! Put it away!

05:21.362 --> 05:23.448
You have to fight it! Just let it go!

05:24.907 --> 05:25.742
No!

05:27.285 --> 05:29.370
What are you doing? Stop!

05:29.454 --> 05:33.374
Don't, please! No! No!

05:34.000 --> 05:34.834
No!

05:38.087 --> 05:40.923
Get inside! Close the door!

05:41.007 --> 05:45.803
There are two people I want dead, okay?

05:45.887 --> 05:47.805
First is Choi Hyeong-wook.

05:47.889 --> 05:49.724
You're a given.

05:50.808 --> 05:52.185
No.

06:00.318 --> 06:05.865
GIRIGO
YOUR WISH HAS BEEN GRANTED

06:06.616 --> 06:08.201
YOUR WISH HAS BEEN GRANTED

06:23.633 --> 06:25.927
IF WISHES COULD KILL

06:44.445 --> 06:46.280
DONG-JAE

06:47.740 --> 06:50.493
The person
you are trying to reach is unavailable.

06:53.204 --> 06:55.498
-The person you are trying--
-Shit! Damn!

07:02.547 --> 07:04.006
REST IN PEACE

07:04.090 --> 07:07.218
And the next is Dong-jae,
who's pissing me off,

07:07.301 --> 07:10.179
and been a jerk all night,
and won't shut up…

07:23.901 --> 07:25.653
-Did you guys hear?
-What?

07:25.736 --> 07:27.363
Hyeong-wook died because of Na-ri.

07:27.447 --> 07:29.115
-She's so gross!
-No way.

07:29.198 --> 07:30.950
Why did Hyeong-wook have to die?

07:31.033 --> 07:33.703
-I wish Na-ri had died instead.
-I know.

07:33.786 --> 07:37.165
Does that mean Se-ah's also
in danger? Na-ri was hitting on Geon-woo.

07:37.248 --> 07:39.834
She's like her mom.
She cheated on her dad and moved away.

07:39.917 --> 07:42.503
-That's her dad.
-That's what Se-ah said.

07:42.587 --> 07:44.505
I guess her family's just that fucked up.

07:44.589 --> 07:46.632
You fucking bitches!

08:12.825 --> 08:14.160
HEE-JIN

08:31.969 --> 08:34.305
-Did the timer appear?
-The timer?

08:43.564 --> 08:45.483
Did your training really get canceled?

08:45.566 --> 08:48.611
So, your wish… came true?

08:49.904 --> 08:52.949
…is canceled. Training is canceled.
Training is canceled!

08:53.032 --> 08:55.910
-Please grant Geon-woo's wish!
-Training is canceled!

08:59.288 --> 09:01.499
-When did your coach cancel?
-11:26.

09:02.708 --> 09:04.335
The message showed up at that time too?

09:04.418 --> 09:06.087
-Mm-hmm.
-You sure it's not a hacker?

09:06.170 --> 09:09.298
It's not. This isn't
some stupid hacking thing.

09:09.799 --> 09:12.134
I saw what it did to Hyeong-wook in class.

09:12.218 --> 09:14.679
Are you saying this app is a murderer?

09:14.762 --> 09:17.473
That you put this thing on your phone
to grants wishes,

09:17.557 --> 09:19.600
and when your wish comes true,
a timer appears,

09:19.684 --> 09:21.894
and it forces you to kill yourself
when it runs out?

09:21.978 --> 09:25.398
We're right back to square one.
This isn't the usual kind of app.

09:26.691 --> 09:28.442
The timer's still going.

09:30.820 --> 09:33.197
If we break the phone, will it stop it?

09:33.281 --> 09:36.367
No, the app won't stop working
just 'cause your phone does.

09:47.128 --> 09:50.715
-Oh!
-Guys. I'll go home and get my laptop.

09:50.798 --> 09:53.426
We need to take a closer look
and see how this app is designed.

09:53.926 --> 09:54.844
Okay.

09:55.595 --> 09:57.972
How about we all get together at my house?

09:59.181 --> 10:00.308
Na-ri?

10:00.891 --> 10:01.726
Huh?

10:02.226 --> 10:03.686
You're with us, right?

10:05.271 --> 10:06.188
Of course.

10:06.772 --> 10:07.857
I'll be there.

10:25.583 --> 10:27.501
Na-ri?

10:28.252 --> 10:31.047
Why didn't you fucking answer your phone?

10:31.130 --> 10:32.757
What are you doing? Please stop!

10:38.888 --> 10:39.847
Get out!

10:51.776 --> 10:53.486
I said get out!

10:57.114 --> 10:58.741
You knew this would happen, didn't you?

11:03.746 --> 11:06.290
I get why Dong-jae was talking shit,
because he was drunk,

11:06.374 --> 11:07.500
but what about your reaction?

11:07.583 --> 11:09.335
I never expected this. That's the truth!

11:09.418 --> 11:11.462
I didn't know Dong-jae would end up dead.

11:11.545 --> 11:13.547
I would've done anything
to stop what you did!

11:13.631 --> 11:16.050
Or maybe you were scared
that I would say your name too.

11:16.842 --> 11:20.596
Na-ri, you also didn't really believe
in the app when you made that wish.

11:20.680 --> 11:23.933
You fucking knew about Girigo,
and you let things go too far!

11:26.018 --> 11:27.770
There was a girl named Kwon Si-won

11:27.853 --> 11:30.231
who made that app
to bully a girl named Do Hye-ryung.

11:30.314 --> 11:33.275
And because of that app,
Do Hye-ryung died.

11:39.907 --> 11:41.117
What about this?

11:43.369 --> 11:44.412
What is that?

11:49.208 --> 11:51.168
The app I saw didn't have a clock.

11:53.379 --> 11:55.297
How did Do Hye-ryung die?

11:55.965 --> 11:57.133
Suicide.

11:59.552 --> 12:02.763
At the time, people were saying there was
no way it could've been a suicide.

12:02.847 --> 12:04.432
But that was just a rumor.

12:04.515 --> 12:08.185
If it's just rumors, then why the fuck
are people still dying?!

12:08.769 --> 12:10.354
I don't know. I'm sorry.

12:12.064 --> 12:13.607
All I can tell you is,

12:14.108 --> 12:16.986
if you really want to know
more about Girigo and when it began,

12:17.570 --> 12:20.030
you should start
by looking into who Kwon Si-won was.

12:20.114 --> 12:23.492
She created Girigo,
and was also a shaman's daughter.

12:24.118 --> 12:25.619
Kwon Si-won?

12:28.080 --> 12:29.540
Ha-joon!

12:32.626 --> 12:33.753
Wait a sec.

12:39.008 --> 12:40.259
Do you believe what Se-ah said?

12:42.011 --> 12:44.930
That Hyeong-wook died
because that app is cursed?

12:46.390 --> 12:48.100
I don't believe in superstitions.

12:49.643 --> 12:50.561
So?

12:51.437 --> 12:53.606
What do you think the app really is, then?

12:55.483 --> 12:58.486
The most logical explanation
would be it's a phishing app.

12:59.195 --> 13:00.821
Hacking, like you said earlier.

13:01.906 --> 13:04.533
Then why didn't you stick up for me
in front of the others?

13:08.329 --> 13:10.372
Do you still have a crush on Se-ah?

13:11.457 --> 13:13.375
Do you still have a crush on Geon-woo?

13:16.253 --> 13:20.841
Anything about the timer? Can you turn it
off or delete it when you do the reset?

13:21.342 --> 13:22.176
Mm.

13:25.387 --> 13:26.347
You're sure?

13:26.430 --> 13:28.724
Uh-huh. I want this to be over.

13:55.251 --> 13:57.461
Geon-woo, are you crying?

13:59.046 --> 13:59.922
No, I…

14:01.090 --> 14:04.927
-I… I got something in my eye.
-Go run it under cold water, or--

14:13.894 --> 14:15.437
Leave me alone.

14:16.146 --> 14:17.064
Geon-woo?

14:17.147 --> 14:19.233
What's happening?

15:04.612 --> 15:06.363
Stop it.

15:27.176 --> 15:29.053
Na-ri! Do you know where you are?

15:32.431 --> 15:33.515
Do you know who I am?

15:35.017 --> 15:36.310
You're Se-ah's aunt.

15:37.311 --> 15:40.564
But h… how did I get here?

15:41.065 --> 15:43.901
So you don't know how you got
to the hospital? With your friends.

15:46.904 --> 15:48.405
Any headaches?

15:48.989 --> 15:50.199
No, I'm okay.

15:50.282 --> 15:52.242
If everything looks stable,

15:52.326 --> 15:55.079
you can take a short rest,
and you'll be able to go.

16:13.847 --> 16:17.476
Geon-woo's parents are here. If they
saw you, they would lose their shit.

16:18.686 --> 16:21.939
Do you need stuff? Some clothes,
or your toothbrush, or whatever?

16:22.648 --> 16:23.607
No, thanks.

16:24.650 --> 16:27.069
I have everything I need.
My aunt brought it.

16:29.446 --> 16:30.572
What about you?

16:31.073 --> 16:32.825
Isn't all your stuff at my place?

16:32.908 --> 16:34.618
Stop by whenever you want.

16:35.244 --> 16:36.704
The code is my birthday.

17:07.234 --> 17:08.110
Hm?

17:08.861 --> 17:11.321
Why did the timer stop?

17:21.707 --> 17:23.375
Oh. Na-ri?

17:24.209 --> 17:25.210
Na-ri!

17:27.129 --> 17:28.672
You still haven't gone home?

17:29.840 --> 17:30.799
Not yet.

17:30.883 --> 17:34.553
Oh, you're looking for Geon-woo?
He's not in the ICU anymore.

17:34.636 --> 17:35.554
Really?

17:36.055 --> 17:38.640
He's much better,
so we moved him to another ward.

17:39.349 --> 17:42.394
Oh, thank God. That's great news!

17:43.062 --> 17:44.605
How is he doing now?

17:45.481 --> 17:47.858
He regained consciousness
about an hour ago.

17:47.941 --> 17:49.693
You can see him. He's allowed visitors.

17:50.444 --> 17:51.528
Na-ri, wait!

17:52.237 --> 17:53.739
If you run into my niece,

17:53.822 --> 17:56.283
can you tell her
that I'm looking for her, please?

17:56.366 --> 17:59.328
She's not in her hospital room,
and I can't get ahold of her.

17:59.411 --> 18:00.662
Great. I'll do that.

18:17.221 --> 18:18.263
Se-ah?

18:19.723 --> 18:21.141
Are you here?

18:32.486 --> 18:35.322
"The timer doesn't stop."

18:41.829 --> 18:43.747
Hyeong-wook died at

18:44.915 --> 18:46.625
9:08.

18:50.671 --> 18:53.382
-When did your coach cancel?
-11:26.

18:53.465 --> 18:57.636
Geon-woo's wish was granted at 11:26.

18:57.719 --> 19:02.141
If you subtract two hours and 18 minutes
from the 24 hours on the timer,

19:02.224 --> 19:05.394
that's 21 hours and 42 minutes.

19:06.436 --> 19:08.897
The same time my timer stopped.

19:12.109 --> 19:14.236
After Geon-woo's wish came true,

19:14.319 --> 19:16.989
that's when my timer also ended.

19:17.948 --> 19:20.284
But then, why did Geon-woo's timer stop?

19:20.868 --> 19:24.830
If I take 11:26,
which is the time of Geon-woo's wish…

19:28.041 --> 19:30.669
He regained consciousness
about an hour ago.

19:31.170 --> 19:34.965
…and subtract the time he woke up,
which was around 9:32,

19:35.048 --> 19:36.967
that's ten hours and six minutes.

19:37.050 --> 19:41.346
If you subtract ten hours and six minutes
from Geon-woo's timer,

19:41.430 --> 19:44.308
you get 13 hours and 54 minutes.

19:46.351 --> 19:48.437
Exactly when Geon-woo woke up.

19:49.188 --> 19:50.939
And again, the timer stopped.

19:51.023 --> 19:52.316
It's funny.

19:53.859 --> 19:55.819
I keep hoping we'll wake up.

19:56.820 --> 19:58.071
Then Se-ah

19:58.572 --> 20:00.365
must have made her own wish.

20:04.077 --> 20:05.245
THE TIMER DOESN'T STOP

20:05.329 --> 20:07.789
So when a new timer begins,

20:09.249 --> 20:11.418
the previous person's timer ends.

20:14.588 --> 20:15.881
SE-AH

20:17.591 --> 20:20.385
The person
you are trying to reach is unavailable.

20:20.469 --> 20:22.346
Please try again later.

20:29.853 --> 20:31.146
HA-JOON

20:33.690 --> 20:35.901
No! I said no!

20:37.486 --> 20:40.864
It's all over for both of us if the door
closes. You need to find a better way.

20:40.948 --> 20:42.032
NA-RI

20:42.115 --> 20:43.158
Understand?

20:43.242 --> 20:45.994
The person
you are trying to reach is unavailable.

20:46.078 --> 20:47.746
Please try again later.

20:49.748 --> 20:52.167
SE-AH, I FOUND A WAY
THERE'S A WAY TO STOP THE TIMER

20:53.710 --> 20:56.380
AND I HAVE A CONFESSION TO MAKE TO YOU

20:57.047 --> 21:00.717
HYEONG-WOOK ACTUALLY…

21:11.061 --> 21:12.354
YOO SE-AH

21:13.563 --> 21:16.316
GEON-WOO, I FOUND A WAY TO STOP THE TIMER!

21:18.652 --> 21:20.195
BUT KEEP THIS A SECRET FROM NA-RI

21:20.279 --> 21:22.155
NOT ALL THREE OF US CAN MAKE IT OUT ALIVE

21:27.369 --> 21:30.664
HOW DO YOU STOP IT?

21:32.666 --> 21:34.918
I'LL TELL YOU IN PERSON, WAIT

21:45.012 --> 21:46.805
This is a fucking nightmare!

21:50.809 --> 21:52.185
YOO SE-AH

21:55.772 --> 21:56.648
Fuck!

22:00.110 --> 22:00.944
Fuck!

22:17.669 --> 22:20.422
Who should I strangle first?
Se-ah or Ha-joon?

22:21.882 --> 22:25.427
Judging by the way they're both
ignoring me, they must be together now.

23:40.001 --> 23:41.128
Hey! Oh…

23:41.795 --> 23:43.171
What are you doing here?

23:43.255 --> 23:45.715
Se-ah's aunt asked me
to run an errand for her.

23:45.799 --> 23:47.300
What are you…

23:47.384 --> 23:48.969
Let's talk inside.

23:55.767 --> 23:59.521
If you're just gonna keep being boring
like this, I'm out. Give me my phone.

24:05.152 --> 24:07.612
I remembered something
while watching the video you took.

24:07.696 --> 24:09.448
The day I went to the hospital…

24:16.246 --> 24:17.247
It was there.

24:19.416 --> 24:21.376
There was someone else here besides us.

24:26.673 --> 24:28.925
Stop! You're scaring me.

24:29.718 --> 24:31.803
She had a huge cut on her face.

24:32.554 --> 24:34.097
And she was wearing our school uniform.

24:34.181 --> 24:37.309
She had the same logo and everything,
but I didn't know her.

24:37.392 --> 24:40.645
A huge cut on her face, like a wound?

24:40.729 --> 24:41.563
Mm-hmm.

24:42.647 --> 24:43.982
That's weird.

24:44.065 --> 24:46.860
But if she was in our school,
we would have totally seen her.

24:46.943 --> 24:49.112
I need us
to break into the school tonight.

24:51.406 --> 24:52.240
Breaking in?

24:52.324 --> 24:54.951
I need to make sure
no teachers are around.

24:55.035 --> 24:58.121
And, uh, I'm not comfortable
doing it alone.

24:58.622 --> 25:00.415
Your help would really go a long way.

25:02.417 --> 25:04.544
Mm, okay.

25:05.962 --> 25:09.925
I can't go like this, so let me change,
and just text me when to meet you.

25:10.008 --> 25:12.385
Uh-huh. You're the best, Na-ri.

25:16.973 --> 25:19.434
The last place
where the signal was detected

25:19.518 --> 25:22.938
was Gwangdong Apartments, building 323.

25:23.021 --> 25:24.940
I can't confirm the floor number, though.

25:25.023 --> 25:26.858
Does that mean the phone is offline?

25:26.942 --> 25:28.109
That would be my guess.

25:28.193 --> 25:31.905
These days, if the phone is on,
it can be detected by Wi-Fi or GPS.

25:36.701 --> 25:38.745
WHERE ARE YOU?

25:38.828 --> 25:42.541
WHEN ARE WE MEETING UP?

25:47.087 --> 25:48.672
YOU'LL FIND OUT SOON, NO RUSH

25:48.755 --> 25:51.007
GEON-WOO
I'M THE ONE WHO STOPPED YOUR TIMER :)

25:59.933 --> 26:05.564
ARE WE STILL KEEPING IT A SECRET
FROM NA-RI?

26:09.442 --> 26:12.153
YEAH, NOT ALL THREE OF US
CAN MAKE IT OUT ALIVE

26:33.592 --> 26:35.510
Geon-woo, wait for me!

26:36.303 --> 26:38.346
How did you know
about this hole in the fence here?

26:38.430 --> 26:40.932
-I'm the one who made it.
-Why would you do that?

26:41.558 --> 26:44.811
To help Se-ah crush the nationals.
Let's go through here.

26:50.400 --> 26:53.570
There's a perfectly good path
over there. Why are we going this way?

26:55.196 --> 26:57.115
-Be careful coming down.
-Wait.

27:03.163 --> 27:06.666
-No way.
-Say hello to your little friend.

27:12.255 --> 27:13.715
Wait, now what?

27:19.721 --> 27:22.349
It's not easy
getting someone on the national team.

27:25.644 --> 27:26.686
Through here.

27:33.443 --> 27:35.070
Whoa!

27:39.491 --> 27:41.868
Jesus, you scared me.

28:02.389 --> 28:04.182
When did you and Se-ah start dating?

28:08.144 --> 28:09.104
We're not.

28:10.271 --> 28:13.358
At her house, you entered her passcode
and walked right in.

28:13.441 --> 28:16.319
You're close enough to share passcodes,
which says a lot.

28:16.403 --> 28:17.904
Th… that was only because--

28:17.987 --> 28:20.573
And the wish video you filmed,
you were both having fried chicken.

28:21.074 --> 28:22.784
That was in Se-ah's house.

28:24.035 --> 28:26.413
And from the looks of it,
you were having a great time.

28:28.456 --> 28:29.624
I'm just curious.

28:29.708 --> 28:33.628
If you guys kept sneaking through
secret passageways together at night,

28:34.129 --> 28:35.839
then why not just tell the truth?

28:38.341 --> 28:40.427
It's kinda complicated.

28:41.803 --> 28:44.889
It hasn't been long,
and we haven't been secretive on purpose.

28:44.973 --> 28:45.932
I'm sorry.

28:49.269 --> 28:50.979
It's normal for people to start dating.

28:51.062 --> 28:52.856
It's not normal
that you're apologizing for it.

28:52.939 --> 28:54.899
I wasn't apologizing for dating.

28:54.983 --> 28:58.486
I was apologizing
for lying to you just now.

29:01.281 --> 29:05.201
Hey, I lie to you all the time, okay?
Why would you feel bad about that?

29:05.827 --> 29:07.579
Yeah? Like what?

29:08.246 --> 29:09.122
Hm?

29:09.205 --> 29:12.292
Well, can't you just tell me
one specific lie you told?

29:12.917 --> 29:14.919
Just to you, or in general?

29:16.379 --> 29:17.714
If you lied to me,

29:18.214 --> 29:20.133
you know I'm willing to forgive you.

29:28.057 --> 29:30.602
Everything you think is true is wrong.

29:31.102 --> 29:33.855
I just lied to you right now.
Even my lies are lies.

29:37.275 --> 29:38.443
NURSE'S OFFICE

29:43.865 --> 29:45.533
Well, we made it this far.

29:46.493 --> 29:47.869
But how do we get in?

29:53.625 --> 29:55.752
The nurse's office door is always open.

29:57.086 --> 29:58.630
Oh. Uh…

30:04.219 --> 30:05.470
Ah!

30:06.054 --> 30:08.640
I didn't know
they still held onto these things.

30:08.723 --> 30:13.186
Even years down the road, your information
remains on file. I wonder if I'm in here?

30:13.269 --> 30:14.229
So creepy.

30:14.312 --> 30:16.523
I sure hope
there's not another kid like you.

30:21.361 --> 30:22.695
"Scraped knee,

30:22.779 --> 30:23.780
Choi Ju-a."

30:25.865 --> 30:28.326
"Possible wrist sprain, Ju Da-hae."

30:33.790 --> 30:35.250
"Laceration with bleeding."

30:39.212 --> 30:40.255
"Kwon Si-won."

30:44.342 --> 30:45.343
You found something?

30:49.806 --> 30:50.932
Na-ri,

30:51.933 --> 30:54.143
she had a wound
on the right side of her face.

30:57.313 --> 30:58.606
You saw it too.

31:00.441 --> 31:01.651
The scary girl?

31:07.448 --> 31:10.076
I didn't see it the first time
from the video you took.

31:10.577 --> 31:12.161
But then I watched it over and over.

31:13.872 --> 31:16.416
I know why
you kept filming an empty space.

31:17.083 --> 31:19.460
There was something there,
and you saw it too.

31:21.838 --> 31:24.007
Something was invisible to the others.

31:35.059 --> 31:37.312
I thought you wanted to watch the video
to find your phone.

31:38.271 --> 31:40.899
So you were just pretending
you couldn't lie earlier?

31:42.191 --> 31:44.652
Wow, Geon-woo. I'm seeing you
in a different light.

31:44.736 --> 31:46.696
Are you the one who took my phone? Huh?

31:46.779 --> 31:48.031
I said I didn't.

31:48.656 --> 31:49.532
Is that a lie?

31:54.287 --> 31:55.204
Na-ri,

31:57.081 --> 31:58.875
those lies you've told me,

31:58.958 --> 32:01.127
I'm sure you have a valid reason.

32:02.503 --> 32:05.673
-Let's try to be honest with each other.
-Don't! Get back!

32:06.674 --> 32:09.427
You lured me into an empty school at night
to scare me.

32:09.510 --> 32:12.764
No, listen! I just wanted to find out
if you'd seen that student.

32:12.847 --> 32:14.349
I thought I was the only one!

32:18.603 --> 32:20.980
Take one more step. I dare you.

32:27.403 --> 32:28.613
Brother-in law.

32:39.165 --> 32:42.335
We're the only ones who saw the scary girl
in the video you took.

32:43.169 --> 32:44.796
That means we're in the most danger.

32:44.879 --> 32:47.090
You have no idea how it feels

32:47.590 --> 32:48.925
to get possessed by her.

32:49.634 --> 32:51.344
Na-ri, we need to help each other.

32:51.427 --> 32:53.471
I'll bet Se-ah can see her now.

32:54.263 --> 32:55.223
What?

32:55.306 --> 32:58.309
A lot has happened
while you were unconscious, lover boy.

32:58.393 --> 33:01.437
What? You want me to lie
and say what a good friend she is?

33:04.816 --> 33:05.775
You see that?

33:06.275 --> 33:07.986
What kind of friend says this?

33:08.778 --> 33:09.779
Slow down.

33:10.363 --> 33:13.908
Earlier today, I went to my phone provider
and canceled my number.

33:13.992 --> 33:16.786
I told them it was stolen
and logged out of all my accounts.

33:16.869 --> 33:19.706
I basically wiped my phone number.
It shouldn't exist!

33:20.206 --> 33:22.375
No one can contact me right now.

33:23.126 --> 33:25.253
You're holding a dead phone, Na-ri.

33:32.885 --> 33:34.429
Wow, you're good.

33:35.013 --> 33:36.639
Both Hyeong-wook and I

33:37.515 --> 33:38.766
went through the same thing.

33:38.850 --> 33:41.185
-Phone calls, texts…
-Stay where you are, liar!

33:41.728 --> 33:43.730
You think you know everything?

33:45.398 --> 33:47.025
You wanna know what my wish was?

33:49.610 --> 33:51.529
"Please let Hyeong-wook die."

33:53.614 --> 33:54.866
Don't you dare lie to me.

33:54.949 --> 33:56.159
Already did.

33:56.951 --> 33:58.911
Now, was that the truth or a lie?

34:00.580 --> 34:02.081
I've lost track.

34:02.665 --> 34:04.542
You wanna see my wish video?

34:08.379 --> 34:09.797
Hey! Are… are you okay?

34:09.881 --> 34:11.507
Get off of me!

34:27.231 --> 34:28.775
I told you not to come close.

34:32.445 --> 34:33.613
Na-ri!

34:34.447 --> 34:35.490
Na-ri, wait!

34:57.845 --> 34:59.222
Come on!

34:59.305 --> 35:01.099
Hey!

35:08.648 --> 35:09.607
Hey.

35:16.072 --> 35:19.408
Oh. Na-ri, no! Hey, stop!

35:33.381 --> 35:34.257
GIRIGO
DOWNLOAD

35:38.261 --> 35:40.721
BEGIN DOWNLOAD

36:05.079 --> 36:06.205
Ah.

36:54.253 --> 36:55.296
Get away!

38:27.013 --> 38:28.097
You all right?

38:29.265 --> 38:31.851
-Where's the girl who was with you?
-Who?

38:31.934 --> 38:34.603
-The girl's name you were shouting?
-Who are you?

38:41.986 --> 38:42.987
Stay still.

39:10.389 --> 39:11.766
We're done.

39:13.225 --> 39:14.185
Huh?

39:14.268 --> 39:15.436
What now?

39:30.326 --> 39:31.744
The rules are simple.

39:31.827 --> 39:33.996
You write down your saju and make a wish.

39:36.415 --> 39:38.125
Will it come true?
